240
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:29,670
Mom had got hurt many times in the past
after getting her hopes up. That's why.

241
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:32,610
What are we doing on such a joyous day?
We must celebrate!

242
00:17:32,610 --> 00:17:33,900
Let's have a celebration party! 
Celebration party!

243
00:17:33,910 --> 00:17:36,060
Grandfather, it's 6 am in the morning.
What celebration party?

244
00:17:36,150 --> 00:17:38,300
Does the time matter for a celebration party?

245
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:40,310
Call over people! Call over everybody!

246
00:17:40,310 --> 00:17:42,520
The more people, the better for a celebration.

247
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,720
Let's just celebrate nicely among 
just us, father-in-law.

248
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,820
Ajumma.

249
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:48,020
This woman!

250
00:17:48,390 --> 00:17:50,960
Aigoo, this rascal.

251
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:53,890
What happened here?

252
00:17:53,890 --> 00:17:54,990
What do you think happened?

253
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:56,830
Out of no choice, I had to make some moves.

254
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:58,300
You hurry up and find the USB.

255
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,770
What 'moves'?

256
00:17:59,770 --> 00:18:01,600
Isn't this a crime?

257
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:05,640
Is being there instead of a dead son
some crime? It's a good deed.

258
00:18:06,010 --> 00:18:08,210
The way that family thinks,
even if we say you are not,

259
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:11,370
I reckon they will deceive themselves 
into believing you are the son anyway.

260
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:13,710
Hold on, hold on, just listen to me.

261
00:18:13,810 --> 00:18:17,380
If you are that reluctant, it's enough to
just confess it once you find the USB.

262
00:18:17,380 --> 00:18:20,320
You do fit that family's specifications on 
the missing person and that isn't a lie.

263
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:24,360
You don't know about the test results, 
so you have no responsibility in that.

264
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:26,560
Do you get what I'm talking about?

265
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:28,390
<i>I'm hanging up.</i>

266
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:30,600
<i>Find that USB fast.</i>

267
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,410
<i>Jun Hyeok.</i>

268
00:18:42,710 --> 00:18:44,340
No Jun Hyeok.

269
00:18:47,850 --> 00:18:48,950
Yes.

270
00:18:50,050 --> 00:18:51,520
- Jin A!
- What?

271
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:52,990
Jin A!

272
00:18:52,990 --> 00:18:54,450
What? What?

273
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:58,860
The youngster is really the son.

274
00:18:58,900 --> 00:18:59,960
What?

275
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:03,630
The youngter... is that... family's real son, yes.

276
00:19:04,190 --> 00:19:05,090
Is it so?

277
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:09,500
See that! I had... told you to bite him, right?

278
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:16,110
No, no. Now that the groundwork is set, 
at least from now on... That's it!

279
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:19,040
You too get mentally prepared
at least from now.

280
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:21,980
This... for us, is an opportunity.
Understand?

281
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,750
Whatever, please don't be like this!

282
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:25,650
You are the one who shouldn't be like this.

283
00:19:25,650 --> 00:19:27,490
This is an opportunity, an opportunity.

284
00:19:27,490 --> 00:19:30,420
They say an opportunity is a 'chance'.
You won't know it?

285
00:19:30,420 --> 00:19:32,990
Mom, 'chance' means opportunity in english.

286
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:35,000
Isn't that what I was saying?

287
00:19:35,010 --> 00:19:36,730
An opportunity is a chance.

288
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:38,500
Don't miss the chance, Jin A.

289
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:42,540
Excuse me, I'm here.

290
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:45,100
- Oh, come on in, come on.
- Your daughter?

291
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:45,840
She's at work.

292
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:48,770
This type of celebration, and you 
invited even me. Thank you.

293
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:51,710
Right now, I feel like having a 
3-month celebration party.

294
00:19:51,710 --> 00:19:54,650
Yes, of course. Where do you find
such a happy occasion?

295
00:19:54,650 --> 00:19:59,420
Wondering what if the youngster isn't the 
real son, I was also so badly worrying.

296
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:01,250
I couldn't even get sleep last night.

297
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,090
Ajumma, why wouldn't you get sleep?

298
00:20:03,820 --> 00:20:06,760
Well... Oh, do you need any help?

299
00:20:08,230 --> 00:20:09,330
Jun Hyeok.

300
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:10,800
Uncle.

301
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,740
<i>Exceptional dance, I must say!</i>

302
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:28,410
Having fun like this, the afternoon time flies!

303
00:20:36,490 --> 00:20:37,960
Oh, it's the seal nuna!
(Nuna - Elder sisier, elder girl)

304
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,790
- Come on in. 
- Come on in, come on.

305
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:40,890
<i>Come and sit down.</i>

306
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:44,560
What are you doing?

307
00:20:44,930 --> 00:20:46,030
Let go.

308
00:20:47,130 --> 00:20:48,600
<i>Come, sit down. Sit down.</i>

309
00:20:49,340 --> 00:20:53,740
<i>Come, sit down. Sit.</i>

310
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,280
How can the lead actor sit outside like this?

311
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:35,760
I'm sorry, but can I do a celebration ritual?

312
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:38,880
When we see baseball, the home run hitters
get a good dose of something!

313
00:21:38,970 --> 00:21:40,610
Can I do it just this once?

314
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:44,020
I will, okay?

315
00:21:44,390 --> 00:21:46,960
Cowabanga, dude!

316
00:21:48,060 --> 00:21:49,530
Why no reaction, like this?

317
00:21:49,530 --> 00:21:52,470
Ah, right! You better not forget about
buying me rib-eye steaks.

318
00:21:52,470 --> 00:21:54,600
If you don't wish to be a 
rich kid, recently deceased.

319
00:21:55,030 --> 00:21:57,570
Come to think of it, the name is kinda nice.

320
00:21:57,970 --> 00:21:59,070
Of what?

321
00:21:59,070 --> 00:22:00,540
Rib-eye steak, I mean.

322
00:22:00,540 --> 00:22:02,600
Is it because there's an eye, like a flower?

323
00:22:04,060 --> 00:22:05,660
Rib-eye steak.

324
00:22:06,470 --> 00:22:08,330
Rib-eye steak...

325
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:11,090
Rib-eye steak!

326
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:13,390
Not only is the name pleasant...

327
00:22:13,390 --> 00:22:15,550
but the smell must be great too, right?

328
00:22:16,690 --> 00:22:19,630
Why do you look like that? 
Since a while back?

329
00:22:22,190 --> 00:22:27,330
Towards what, and where to
let myself carry on, and how...

330
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:28,800
isn't very clear.

331
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,820
What are you talking about?

332
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:32,100
Turned rich, and you're already all smug?

333
00:22:32,470 --> 00:22:33,940
Doesn't suit you, okay?

334
00:22:34,670 --> 00:22:37,980
I've seen you in all kinds of shit before,
and you get picky with words now?

335
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:41,650
<i>Jun Hyeok, where did you go?</i>

336
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:49,220
Dad. Quickly bring Jun Hyeok to visit Min Hyeok.

337
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:51,560
Min Hyeok has been looking
for Jun Hyeok for a while.

338
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,390
Okay, I'm hanging up.

339
00:22:54,130 --> 00:22:55,420
You going out somewhere?

340
00:22:55,470 --> 00:22:57,800
- Yeah, a party.
- Party?

341
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:58,830
What party?

342
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:02,200
That "Intro to Civil Engineering" seonbae is 
throwing it, as the movie made it to no.1.

343
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,670
What? The movie is a no. 1 hit?

344
00:23:03,670 --> 00:23:06,240
"One Same Vegas" is that place where
we had an earlier get-together, right?

345
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:09,540
Yeah. There, well... 
You really must go?

346
00:23:09,540 --> 00:23:12,850
My schoolmates will all be there.
I'll just go, show my face and return.

347
00:23:13,210 --> 00:23:15,410
What's the point in just going to show the face?

348
00:23:15,780 --> 00:23:18,720
Why all this interrogation? 
I just have to go, so I will go.

349
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:21,290
There's salad and sandwiches in the fridge.

350
00:23:21,290 --> 00:23:23,120
Don't forget to feed the boys.

351
00:23:27,530 --> 00:23:29,730
Why? You changing into this?

352
00:23:29,730 --> 00:23:30,830
Yeah, this feels a bit too dark.

353
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:33,400
Go out. I want to change.

354
00:23:40,010 --> 00:23:41,470
You going somewhere?

355
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:44,230
I want to take Jun Hyeok to the 
hospital to visit Min Hyeok.

356
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,380
Jun Hyeok.

357
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,360
Yes.

358
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:50,570
He will be extremely happy to see you.

359
00:23:50,650 --> 00:23:54,660
Even as kids, he liked you a lot
and took you out to play.

360
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,830
Yes.

361
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:17,340
<i>What's this small small rise of uneasy feeling
that I keep getting?</i>

362
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:19,280
<i>A suspicious party, out of the blue.</i>

363
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:21,140
<i>A red one-piece dress.</i>

364
00:24:21,850 --> 00:24:23,680
<i>My suspicion the day before must be correct.</i>

365
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,150
<i>That dog-like...</i>

366
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:26,480
<i>Dad.</i>

367
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,900
<i>Dad!</i>

368
00:24:27,990 --> 00:24:29,470
Dad!!

369
00:24:31,020 --> 00:24:32,860
Why are you shaking your legs?

370
00:24:32,940 --> 00:24:36,380
Dad, if you keep shaking your legs,
this will shake too, you know.

371
00:24:37,260 --> 00:24:38,360
Sorry.

372
00:24:40,930 --> 00:24:44,600
<i>Correct. Buried deep... Buried deep...</i>

373
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,810
<i>everybody has a past, don't they all?</i>

374
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:49,380
<i>But a party today?</i>

375
00:24:49,740 --> 00:24:52,310
Dad! Why do you keep shaking?

376
00:24:52,310 --> 00:24:54,880
Dad, don't shake your leg.

377
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,720
This will get shaken!

378
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:03,320
<i>But yes. It's not like it's a solo meeting with him.</i>

379
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:05,520
<i>Won't all the schoolmates be there?</i>

380
00:25:05,890 --> 00:25:08,860
<i>Moreover, it is the No Bo Yeong who
beheads those she can see through.</i>

381
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,760
<i>But what if that fellow keeps 
making his moves...</i>

382
00:25:19,110 --> 00:25:20,210
<i>No Bo Yeong.</i>

383
00:25:20,210 --> 00:25:21,670
Why are you like this?

384
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,340
The old days came to mind.

385
00:25:26,450 --> 00:25:28,280
After all this while, if we return to that...

386
00:25:28,650 --> 00:25:29,380
Seonbae, what are you doing?

387
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:31,580
Think about our Cheongju trip.

388
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:37,410
That's it!

389
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:39,900
- What are you doing? 
- What are you doing, Dad?

390
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:42,960
I have to go out for awhile. 
You guys have your dinner first.

391
00:25:47,370 --> 00:25:52,510
Min Hyeok, after an accident, 
has no recent memories.

392
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:59,480
Till he recovers, you will need to 
take good care of your brother.

393
00:26:04,620 --> 00:26:07,550
Of course, we are on the way to the hospital.

394
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:11,590
Currently crossing the Seongsu bridge.

395
00:26:42,050 --> 00:26:44,620
<i>Child, say goodbye to your mother.</i>

396
00:26:44,620 --> 00:26:46,090
<i>Tell your mother to go in peace.</i>

397
00:26:46,830 --> 00:26:48,290
<i>Mom,</i>

398
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:51,600
<i>Go in peace.</i>

399
00:27:47,390 --> 00:27:48,120
Who is he?

400
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,960
It's Jun Hyeok.

401
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:53,990
The brother you have been yearning for.
Jun Hyeok.

402
00:27:53,990 --> 00:27:55,460
You are Jun Hyeok?

403
00:27:57,300 --> 00:28:00,600
Why are you here only now? 
I had missed you so much.

404
00:28:06,110 --> 00:28:07,940
<i>Why do you look like that?</i>

405
00:28:08,310 --> 00:28:09,780
<i>I don't know...</i>

406
00:28:10,140 --> 00:28:14,180
<i>Towards what, and where to
let myself carry on, and how...</i>

407
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,950
<i>He is not Jun Hyeok.</i>

408
00:28:18,950 --> 00:28:20,050
What?

409
00:28:20,050 --> 00:28:21,430
Why?

410
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:23,720
Isn't he the same one, from the test results?

411
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:24,910
I feel there is some mistake.

412
00:28:24,940 --> 00:28:26,480
Somebody must have done something.

413
00:28:26,660 --> 00:28:29,020
No matter how I look, 
it's not Jun Hyeok. That guy.

414
00:28:34,730 --> 00:28:36,180
Sing together.

415
00:28:39,140 --> 00:28:40,150
Louder!

416
00:28:47,950 --> 00:28:49,050
That bastard.

417
00:28:49,780 --> 00:28:50,930
Hey, you punk!

418
00:28:50,950 --> 00:28:52,280
Won't take your hands off?

419
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,960
You crazy psycho bastard!

420
00:29:02,630 --> 00:29:04,100
Are you crazy? What are you doing?

421
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:05,630
You!

422
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:10,700
Who would you be?

423
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:11,800
What?

424
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,640
There are such mad guys around?

425
00:29:18,410 --> 00:29:19,880
I am a lawyer.

426
00:29:20,610 --> 00:29:22,820
Please let me have a discussion with the victim.

427
00:29:23,180 --> 00:29:25,020
The victim has already lodged a report.

428
00:29:25,020 --> 00:29:26,490
You just stay quiet, over there.

429
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,200
<i>You didn't even feed the boys.
Where are you?</i>

430
00:29:48,140 --> 00:29:51,440
<i>Chan U asked me to have a drink.
I'll be back in a jiffy.</i>

431
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:54,380
Still not letting go? Don't you know
who my husband is?

432
00:29:54,380 --> 00:29:56,580
If I just make a call, all of you are finished. 
Do you know?

433
00:29:56,580 --> 00:29:59,150
- Ajumma. Just be quiet, please! 
- Let go. Let go.

434
00:29:59,150 --> 00:29:59,890
Hold on.

435
00:29:59,890 --> 00:30:01,350
One moment!

436
00:30:06,490 --> 00:30:10,530
Excuse... Excuse me.

437
00:30:11,260 --> 00:30:12,000
What?

438
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:16,400
Aren't you... perhaps Gim Do Sang?

439
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:17,500
You are...?

440
00:30:22,270 --> 00:30:23,380
By any chance...

441
00:30:23,740 --> 00:30:27,050
You remember?
It's me. Su Ji.

442
00:30:27,780 --> 00:30:31,080
In our university days, didn't we join 
the folklore department together?

443
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:44,300
Go Su Ji.

444
00:30:45,770 --> 00:30:47,870
Do Sang oppa.
(oppa - older brother, boyfriend)

445
00:30:51,270 --> 00:30:52,740
Let's do a toast.

446
00:30:52,740 --> 00:30:54,570
- Salut!
- cheers.

447
00:30:57,140 --> 00:30:58,980
<i>This time who will be no. 1?</i>

448
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:03,020
<i>I was watching Taekwando yesterday. 
It's really great.</i>

449
00:31:03,020 --> 00:31:05,220
<i>Keep it up. Keep up the top position.</i>

450
00:31:05,220 --> 00:31:06,690
<i>Boxing and wrestling aren't bad either.</i>

451
00:31:07,790 --> 00:31:09,260
<i>Let's go together.</i>

452
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:11,090
<i>I will be back after a toilet trip.</i>

453
00:31:12,190 --> 00:31:13,290
<i>Wait for me!</i>

454
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:20,630
<i>Initially it was... Gim Dong Yul of the exhibition
that I liked a lot.</i>

455
00:31:22,470 --> 00:31:27,610
<i>From today, oppa, is it okay if I like you...
more than Gim Dong Yul?</i>

456
00:31:28,340 --> 00:31:29,710
<i>Su Ji.</i>

457
00:31:30,910 --> 00:31:34,580
<i>Actually, right from the first time I saw you,</i>

458
00:31:34,580 --> 00:31:41,190
<i>I felt that it's not Gang Su Ji, but you Go Su Ji,
that I found more beautiful.</i>

459
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:02,840
<i>Your... your... your... chin.</i>

460
00:32:03,580 --> 00:32:05,040
No, no, no... You both... Your chins!

461
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:09,450
What do we do?
Please don't!

